[[About|Fiji]] is an image processing package. It can be described as a distribution of [http://imagej.nih.gov/ij ImageJ] (and soon [http://imagejdev.org/ ImageJ2]) together with Java, Java 3D and a lot of plugins organized into a [[Plugins Menu|coherent menu structure]]. Fiji compares to ImageJ as Ubuntu compares to Linux.

The main focus of Fiji is to assist research in life sciences.

For [[Fiji Usage|users]], Fiji is [[Downloads|easy to install]] and has an automatic update function, bundles a [[:Category:Plugins|lot of plugins]] and offers comprehensive [[documentation]].

For [[Developing_Fiji|developers]], Fiji is an open source project hosted in a [[Git for dummies|Git version control]] [http://fiji.sc/cgi-bin/gitweb.cgi repository], with access to the source code of all internals, libraries and plugins, and eases the [[Developing_Fiji|development]] and [[:Category:Scripting|scripting]] of plugins.

